shared_text:
Llano County Office of Emergency Management
Yesterday at 8:16 AM ·

Health Care Access

The pandemic has revealed some serious shortcomings in the US health care system. But without the census, access to hospitals, therapists, reproductive clinics, drugs, and other medical essentials would be even more restricted. Doctors and insurance companies use the demographic information from the survey to build new facilities in areas of need. Epidemiologists, on the other hand, use it to predict hot spots for influenza.

Our goal is to increase self-response rates during Non-Response Follow-Up (NRFU) operations. By self-responding to the Census, residents can stop the knock! Respond today at my2020census.gov or by phone at 1-844-330-2020 (English)/844-468-2020.

LAST DAY TO COMPLETE THE SURVEY -

An Important Announcement from Llano ISD:

Llano ISD would like to remind all parents and students that in order for a student to begin school in-person or remotely on the first day of school (Thursday, August 13), a student MUST be registered for school AND have made an instructional setting selection.

Students that have not registered for school or made an instructional setting selection will not be issued a schedule, classroom assignment, remote curriculum, or be eligible to ride the bus. If you have questions please contact your campus principal.

Please complete this survey by August 4, 2020: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSey0zo-ifAedMO8nU7V6K3f7vBsbYuvF7ENYkec4zsbBC3IoA/viewform?usp=pp_url

LHS will be hosting a Freshman Orientation on Friday 8/7 at LHS. We will be hosting 5 separate 1 hour sessions starting from 12:00 and ending at 4:00. IT WILL BE HERE SOON!!

June 9-11

1st week of Jacket Conditioning

7:30-9am Skills

Main Gym - HS Volleyball - June 9-11 (60 min)

Aux Gym - June 9,11 incoming 7-12 Basketball non volleyball (60 min)
June 10 - softball skills - non vb (60 min)

Once the athlete hits 60 min of one sport if they play multiple they will then see their next sport coach for the remainder of skill time (30 min) of the 90 min total they can have daily , if they just play the one they will rest until S&C starts

9-10am Strength - Conditioning

Parents - please check team app for Volleyball and Basketball to see the rules and guidelines we will follow to make sure all are safe.

We can’t wait to see the kids!!

It’s not mandatory but we hope to see as many as we can.

Have a great weekend!

5:00-6:00

5:00-6:00

shared_text:
Llano Elementary School
January 7 at 3:41 PM ·

According to the CDC, this flu season has seen an elevation in flu cases for the last 8 weeks and IS expected to increase in the weeks to come. There have been many reports on social media about students contracting flu and strep during our 3 week break. As of now, our school is germ free. During our break our school was fogged with hospital grade disinfectant.

Parents, please: launder your students coats, hoodies, gloves and hats frequently. Also clean their backpacks with Lysol or Clorox wipes. (And continue this practice once a week).

Remind your students to sneeze or cough into the crook of their arms. And to WASH THEIR HANDS...constantly.

Do not eat or drink after their friends. Keep their hands off their faces, do not chew on pencils, erasures or other non-edible items.

If your student has a severely running nose, constant cough or fever DO NOT SEND THEM TO SCHOOL. Rather take them to the doctor.

If you have any questions, please call our School Nurse, Marrijane Steelman, 325 248 2235 OR msteelman@llanoisd.org.

Enjoy the rest of your break and stay healthy!!

Texas Department of Public Safety - Southeast Texas Region
August 9, 2019 at 2:05 PM ·

A STOPPED SCHOOL BUS: WHAT DO I DO?

Texas State law requires that drivers stop when a school bus is operating a visual signal-either red flashing lights or extended stop arm (TRC 545.066). However, many Texas drivers are uncertain as to when they need to stop for a school bus.

Here are a few guidelines to reduce driver confusion, thus providing a safer environment for our children. #BackToSchoolSafety

post_text: Due to heavy rain in the area and the National Weather Service prediction of additional rain of 3 or more inches tonight, Llano ISD will delay the start of school by 2 hours on Tuesday, October 16, 2018, as a precautionary measure. Also, buses will run 2 hours later than normal. This delay applies to students and staff. Please be safe traveling to school and do not go around high water barricades. An update will be sent if the situation worsens and other changes become necessary. Note that breakfast will not be served due to the late start.
